      },
      "date": "2019-10-04 22:36:47.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHow does this compare with Patrick's old patch https://review.whamcloud.com/34186 \"LU-10589 tests: Log nested tests differently\"?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "202e7eeed1c44969ef3359e59448a1604e17cb78",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2019-10-04 22:42:54.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "cb1354aca391271353288987da0c0a72a445c401",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 292,
        "name": "James Nunez",
        "email": "jnunez@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jnunez"
      },
      "date": "2019-10-04 22:44:19.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nPatrick's patch changes how we report results for \"nested\" test suites and could still be used with this patch. I'm not sure what elements of Patrick's patch we want and will it cause any confusion when looking at the test results. Since I'm not sure how to move Patrick's patch forward, this patch is a quick fix that will, is a sanity or sanityn subtest fails, stop the last subtest in that suite to incorrectly report that it failed too. \n\nSo, with this patch, Patrick's patch is still relevant. His patch could make this one unnecessary, depending on how it is implemented.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "12e561dfa365acb097610221ccd8adbdbaa51438",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 377,
        "name": "wc-checkpatch",
        "username": "hpdd-checkpatch",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2019-10-09 23:23:14.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nThis change cannot be cherry-picked to master.\nPlease rebase the change locally and upload the rebased commit for review.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
