    {
      "id": "85dc5635357dfd92f399426cd41811ea187742ae",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 292,
        "name": "James Nunez",
        "email": "jnunez@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jnunez"
      },
      "date": "2019-11-20 21:40:19.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nSure. The problem is that, when an individual test fails in sanity, the whole test suite is marked as failing, but this results in the last test in sanity being marked as failed. See https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/870c7a78-467f-11e9-9646-52540065bddc and many other failures to see what happens when a sanity test in sanity-dom fails. So, this patch is actually to stop sanity-dom/sanity test 251 from being marked as failed when it does not fail.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
